### INITIALIZE&#95;PASS() {#af4707f2d4fe8e86f046089a400af7e72}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>INITIALIZE&#95;PASS (RISCVVectorPeephole, <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/adt/genericcycleimpl-h/#ad78e062f62e0d6e453941fb4ca843e4d">DEBUG&#95;TYPE</a>, &quot;RISC-V Fold Masks&quot;, false, false)</>}>
Given <code><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/user">User</a></code> that has an input operand with EEW=SEW, which uses the dest operand of <code>Src</code> with an unknown EEW, return true if their EEWs match.

Convert unit strided unmasked loads and stores to whole-register equivalents to avoid the dependency on $vl and $vtype.

x = PseudoVLE8&#95;V&#95;M1 passthru, ptr, vlmax, policy PseudoVSE8&#95;V&#95;M1 v, ptr, vlmax

-&gt;

x = VL1RE8&#95;V ptr VS1R&#95;V v, ptr

</MemberDefinition>

<Link id="l00101" /><CodeLine lineNumber="101"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Attempt to reduce the VL of an instruction whose sole use is feeding a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00102" /><CodeLine lineNumber="102"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// instruction with a narrower VL.  This currently works backwards from the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00103" /><CodeLine lineNumber="103"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// user instruction (which might have a smaller VL).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00104" /><CodeLine lineNumber="104"><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">bool</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> RISCVVectorPeephole::tryToReduceVL(<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machineinstr">MachineInstr</a> &amp;<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/codegen/lib/codegen/globalisel/irtranslator-cpp/#abe44dfdea65b4f7e11e0a608ab708b76">MI</a>)</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword"> const </span><span class="doxyHighlight">&#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00105" /><CodeLine lineNumber="105"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Note that the goal here is a bit multifaceted.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00106" /><CodeLine lineNumber="106"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// 1) For store&#39;s reducing the VL of the value being stored may help to</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00107" /><CodeLine lineNumber="107"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    reduce VL toggles.  This is somewhat of an artifact of the fact we</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00108" /><CodeLine lineNumber="108"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    promote arithmetic instructions but VL predicate stores.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00109" /><CodeLine lineNumber="109"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// 2) For vmv.v.v reducing VL eagerly on the source instruction allows us</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00110" /><CodeLine lineNumber="110"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    to share code with the foldVMV&#95;V&#95;V transform below.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00111" /><CodeLine lineNumber="111"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00112" /><CodeLine lineNumber="112"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Note that to the best of our knowledge, reducing VL is generally not</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00113" /><CodeLine lineNumber="113"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// a significant win on real hardware unless we can also reduce LMUL which</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00114" /><CodeLine lineNumber="114"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// this code doesn&#39;t try to do.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00115" /><CodeLine lineNumber="115"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00116" /><CodeLine lineNumber="116"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// TODO: We can handle a bunch more instructions here, and probably</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00117" /><CodeLine lineNumber="117"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// recurse backwards through operands too.</span></CodeLine>
